A CITY theatre is hosting a large-scale exhibition. Theatre set to host giant art exhibition A CITY theatre is hosting a large-scale exhibition.Turner Prize nominee Mike Nelson will exhibit his giant sculptures at the Tramway from November 15.Fans will get the chance to see the artist's best known work, the Coral Reef, which was recently displayed in London's Tate Modern gallery.The exhibition focusers around Mike's time travelling through Canada and the human connection with the great outdoors.He also draws inspiration from Canadian and Scottish nature.The free exhibition will be on display until January 11, 2015. 